&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Stun!&quot; the leader cried above the havoc, and the enchanter moved close to the fighting mob once more, placing herself near his thrusting claws. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Her startled cry alerted all that the claws had gotten her, and her incantation ceased as she tried to gather her concentration once more. But again the creature clawed, wounding her; and again. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Superior heal,&quot; the cleric said, his soft voice both reassuring and calm amonst the frenzy of the battle being waged.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The enchanter calmed, and carefully recited the words she needed and cast, this time stunning the still screaming foe. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp The spell hit the mob hard, ceasing movement, and the warriors once more attacked with vigour, sending the target to the ground with its last fateful cry....<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Closing her eyes for a moment, the high elf watched as the warriors took from the dead all it had to offer. &quot;Sit and heal,&quot; one of them said gently, and she nodded, moving to the back wall of the small tunnel.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Mana?&quot; their leader asked.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp All casters in their party responded, but when her turn, the young enchanter hung her head. &quot;I am very low...that last one took all I had left....&quot;<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Rest then,&quot; came a soft voice from beside her.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Looking up, her eyes widened slightly as she met the dark eyes of a stranger. His deep blue skin darkened in the dimly lit tunnel they sat in, but she saw that he smiled. She watched his lips move slowly as he cast, and a moment later she felt a chill sweep through her as he filled her with his own mana. A necromancer. <br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Thank you,&quot; she said softly, startled by the change in her voice.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;Anytime,&quot; he replied, but his eyes never left her.<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp Closing her eyes, she tried to concentrate on the restoration of her magical forces, but her mind was distracted -- so distracted she could hardly think. However, much to her surprise, his soft voice remained inside her head, and the words were clear and distinct....<br>
&nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &nbsp &quot;You are mine,&quot; he said softly, &quot;and I am yours....&quot;<br>
